-- 
Enerjisa Raises Capacity to 1,557 MW With New Hydro Power Plant

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-03-27T14:44:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-27/enerjisa-raises-capacity-to-1-557-mw-with-new-hydro-power-plant.html
Enerjisa Enerji Uretim AS, the
Turkish utility owned by Austrian power company  Verbund AG (VER)  and
 Haci Omer Sabanci Holding AS (SAHOL) , raised its capacity to 1,557
megawatts with the opening of a new plant today.  The Hacininoglu regulator and hydroelectric plant in the
southeastern Turkish city of Kahramanmaras adds 142 megawatts to
Enerjisa’s production capacity and cost 120 million euros ($170
million) to build, Enerjisa said in an e-mailed statement.  Enerjisa will open another 85 megawatt hydroelectric plant
at the Menge Dam by the end of the year, and a 39 megawatt wind
energy plant in 2012, the statement said. The company aims to
more than triple capacity to at least 5,000 megawatts in 2015,
it said.  Today’s opening ceremony was attended by Prime Minister
 Recep Tayyip Erdogan , Energy Minister Taner Yildiz, Sabanci
Holding Chairwoman Guler Sabanci and Verbund board member Ulrike Baumgartner-Gabitzer.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
Benjamin Harvey at 
 bharvey11@bloomberg.net  